div.p:
Whether just as God is able 
to make something please from what is not 
while not giving it a lack of infused charity, 
so he by himself able to make one dear 
from what is not by withdrawing the rectitude of the human will; 
whether just as God 
is able to make one dear from what is not dear, 
so he by himself is able to make one just from what is not just;
whether just as God is able to make one pleasing 
from what is not while not putting charity in the human mind, 
so is he by himself able to make one dear from what is not 
dear in removing the charity from an already possessed charity.
